starring Sandra Oh is elevated by a novel parenting crisis culturally specific workplace issues and irrepressible romantic chemistry.";i:11;s:25:"The Chair Netflix review.";i:12;s:71:"Finally we have a worthy showcase for Sandra Ohs cracking comic timing.";i:13;s:84:"In Netflixs new dramedy The Chair Sandra Oh plays Dr Ji-Yoon Kim the new chair of a.";i:14;s:98:"The Chair is exactly the kind of whip-smart laugh out loud dramedy we need in our lives right now.";i:15;s:98:"The cast is amazing and although it touches on serious topics it never takes itself too seriously.";i:16;s:68:"My only problem with The Chair is that theres just not enough of it.";i:17;s:127:"It feels like the six episodes fly by and by the closing credits were only just getting to know the people of Pembroke College.";i:18;s:72:"So far reviews for Netflixs The Chair have been overwhelmingly positive.";i:19;s:72:"Its release timed as a new school year begins could not be more perfect.";i:20;s:94:"Season 1 of the series came out on August 20 and the internet has been buzzing about it since.";i:21;s:47:"The Chair is a fun bingeable workplace dramedy.";i:22;s:175:"But that its being hailed as satire says more about the overlapping class politics of the media and tenured faculty as culture industry workers than about its biting politics.";i:23;s:25:"August 24 2021 at 614 pm.";i:24;s:187:"One of the great strengths of The Chair Netflix is its vivid evocation of the requirements for survival in this place where a packed lecture hall and a youthful instructor count for more.";i:25;s:193:"The Chair is a nice tidy six-episode binge and at about three hours total it feels like a slightly extended indie-film comedy set to a soundtrack of jangly college radio hits from the likes of.";i:26;s:76:"There is a poignant pleasure to be found in loving something past its prime.";i:27;s:117:"Watching The Chair a Netflix limited series in which Sandra Oh plays an academic struggling to stave off the decline.";i:28;s:106